urlText: Major Event Buses operating for P!NK concert at Olympic Park
content:
Saturday 16 March
  • From 3.30pm till midnight, Sydney Olympic Park Major Event Buses will run for the P!NK concert at Accor Stadium.
  • Travel on the Major Event Buses is included in the cost of tickets to the P!NK concert only. Attendees do not need to tap on and off, simply show your concert ticket to the driver when boarding buses
  • Buses run every 5 to 20 minutes, subject to traffic conditions.
  • Note: buses will not leave Olympic Park until the concert has finished, expected from approximately 11pm. Passengers boarding services prior to the end of the show will need to wait until the concert has finished before the bus departs.
  • For more information on transport options to the event, see the P!NK concert event page.

All other stops remain the same.
 
For more information see the news story.
 
This change will improve journey time and reliability for passengers and will allow drivers to complete other routes impacted by driver shortages.
 
Plan your trip with Trip Planner or transport apps before you travel.

urlText: Lakemba bus diversions for Ramadan Street Market
content:
Saturday 9 March to Monday 8 April
  • Nightly from 5pm until 3am, route 946 services will be diverting and missing stops while road closures are in place for Ramadan Nights around Lakemba Station.
  • Services towards Roselands will divert via Quigg St and the Boulevarde. Catch buses to Roselands from Lakemba Station, Haldon St, Stand A (219515) or Canterbury Rd before Dennis St (219517).
  • Services towards Bankstown will divert via the Boulevarde and Quigg St. Catch buses to Bankstown from Canterbury Rd at Legge St (2196258) or Lakemba Station, Haldon St, Stand B (219514).
  • Check signs at bus stops for alternative stop locations. For more transport information, see the Ramadan Nights event page.
Missed bus stops:

  • Haldon St before Grace Ave (219595)
